Gleb Ebert

About me

My name is Gleb Ebert and I am a doctoral student in the evolutionary microbiology group at ETH Zurich. I am interested in fundamental aspects of microbial evolution, which I aim to investigate using experimental evolution and genomics approaches. In particular, my PhD research concerns with the upper limits of thermal adaptation of Pseudoalteromonas haloplanktis, an antarctic marine bacterium.

I also enjoy photography and birding, even though I don’t manage to go out often.

Education

2021 - present | PhD in Environmental Sciences, ETH Zurich, Switzerland

2019 - 2021 | MSc in Biology (Major in Microbiology and Immunology), ETH Zurich, Switzerland

2016 - 2020 | BSc in Biology, ETH Zurich, Switzerland

Resources

Throughout my bachelor studies in biology at ETH Zurich, I compiled notes for many of the lectures. They can be found here.
